Vice President Kamala Harris welcomed Israeli President Isaac Herzog to her office in Washington, D.C. They discussed the importance of the relationship between the United States and Israel, as well as their shared commitment to Israel's security. They also announced a joint investment of $70 million for new food security and climate resilience initiatives in the Middle East and Africa. The initiative will focus on deploying Israeli and American technology to farmers and innovators, including water efficiency technologies and mobile apps to monitor crop health. They also discussed their work to promote an integrated and interconnected Middle East, counter the threats posed by Iran, and ensure the safety and security of Israelis and Palestinians. President Herzog praised Vice President Harris for her lifelong contribution to the bonds between the two nations and thanked her husband, Doug Emhoff, for his efforts to combat antisemitism and hatred. They both expressed their commitment to addressing the climate crisis and working towards a renewable Middle East.